      • parse

        public java.sql.Timestamp parse(java.lang.String pathfile,
                                java.lang.String nnsssss,
                                double rate,
                                java.sql.Timestamp lastconverted,
                                RawInputClient raw)
        Parses the campbell digitizer data and updates edge server.
        Parameters:
        pathfile - String of path to the data file and its name.
        nnsssss - Network and station name.
        rate - Sampling rate (usually 15 minutes for landslide data). Negative values indicate period in seconds.
        lastconverted - The most recent recorded converted. Comes from landslideconfig table entries.
        raw - The RawInputClient used to send data to edge.
        Returns:
        New lastconverted timestamp used to update the SQL table.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
                 throws java.lang.InstantiationException
        Main method. Initializes properties, establishes DBConnectionThread, parses data for each configured Campbell digitizer, computes metadata constants and updates their SQL table.
        Parameters:
        args - Can be -s sname to only parse a single station, -test to parse entire dataset regardless of epoch, or -rbmd to rebuild the metadata table.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InstantiationException
